{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/test/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"df89427b-5066-5675-9e31-1f3a27fb393c","excerpt":"gatsby-remark-katex adds math equation support to gatsby using\nremark-math and katex. Math Equations in Inline Mode Surround your equation with  to generate aâ€¦","html":"<p><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/plugins/gatsby-remark-katex/\">gatsby-remark-katex</a> adds math equation support to gatsby using\n<a href=\"https://github.com/Rokt33r/remark-math\">remark-math</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/Khan/KaTeX\">katex</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"math-equations-in-inline-mode\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#math-equations-in-inline-mode\" aria-label=\"math equations in inline mode permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Math Equations in Inline Mode</h2>\n<p>Surround your equation with <code class=\"language-text\">$</code> to generate a math equation in inline mode.</p>\n<p><strong>Example markdown:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$a^2 + b^2 = c^2$</code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>Example output:</strong> $a^2 + b^2 = c^2$</p>\n<h2 id=\"math-equations-in-display-mode\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#math-equations-in-display-mode\" aria-label=\"math equations in display mode permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Math Equations in Display Mode</h2>\n<p>Surround your equation with <code class=\"language-text\">$$</code> and new-lines to generate a math equation in\ndisplay mode.</p>\n<p><strong>Example markdown:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$$\na^2 + b^2 = c^2\n$$</code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>Example output:</strong></p>\n<p>$$\na^2 + b^2 = c^2\n$$</p>\n<p><strong>Add Katex CSS to your template</strong> Katex's CSS file is required to render the\nformulas correctly. Include the CSS file in your template (<a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/blob/master/examples/using-remark/src/templates/template-blog-post.js\">example</a>)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">require(`katex/dist/katex.min.css`)</code></pre></div>\n<div>\n  <article class=\"print:hidden\">\n    <h2>My Secret Pizza Recipe</h2>\n    <p>This recipe is a secret, and must not be shared with anyone</p>\n  </article>\n  <div class=\"hidden font-bold print:flex justify-center text-white cursor-pointer bg-indigo-400 p-2 rounded mt-1\">\n    Are you seriously trying to print this? It's secret!\n  </div>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Rendering math equations with KaTeX","date":"August 07, 2017","description":null}}},"pageContext":{"id":"df89427b-5066-5675-9e31-1f3a27fb393c"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"],"slicesMap":{}}